inetMRouteStdMIB.description: The MIB module for management of IP Multicast routing, but independent of the specific multicast routing protocol in use.

LanguageTag.name: LanguageTag
LanguageTag.description: An RFC 1766-style language tag, with all alphabetic characters converted to lowercase. This restriction is intended to make the lexical ordering imposed by SNMP useful when applied to language tags. Note that it is theoretically possible for a valid language tag to exceed the allowed length of this syntax, and thus be impossible to represent with this syntax. Sampling of language tags in current use on the Internet suggests that this limit does not pose a serious problem in practice.

inetMRouteEnabled.name: inetMRouteEnabled
inetMRouteEnabled.description: The enabled status of IP Multicast routing on this router.

inetMRouteEntryCount.name: inetMRouteEntryCount
inetMRouteEntryCount.description: The number of rows in the inetMRouteTable. This can be used to monitor the multicast routing table size.

inetMRouteTable.name: inetMRouteTable
inetMRouteTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing multicast routing information for IP datagrams sent by particular sources to the IP multicast groups known to this router.

inetMRouteEntry.name: inetMRouteEntry
inetMRouteEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the multicast routing information for IP datagrams from a particular source and addressed to a particular IP multicast group address. Discontinuities in counters in this entry can be detected by observing the value of inetMRouteUpTime.

inetMRouteGroupType.name: inetMRouteGroupType
inetMRouteGroupType.description: A value indicating the address family of the address contained in inetMRouteGroup. Legal values correspond to the subset of address families for which multicast forwarding is supported.

inetMRouteGroup.name: inetMRouteGroup
inetMRouteGroup.description: The IP multicast group address which when combined with the corresponding value specified in inetMRouteGroupMaskLen identifies the groups for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

inetMRouteGroupMaskLen.name: inetMRouteGroupMaskLen
inetMRouteGroupMaskLen.description: The length in bits of the mask which when combined with the corresponding value of inetMRouteGroup identifies the groups for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

inetMRouteSourceType.name: inetMRouteSourceType
inetMRouteSourceType.description: A value indicating the address family of the address contained in inetMRouteSource. The value MUST be the same as the value of inetMRouteGroupType.

inetMRouteSource.name: inetMRouteSource
inetMRouteSource.description: The network address which when combined with the corresponding value of inetMRouteSourceMaskLen identifies the sources for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

inetMRouteSourceMaskLen.name: inetMRouteSourceMaskLen
inetMRouteSourceMaskLen.description: The length in bits of the mask which when combined with the corresponding value of inetMRouteSource identifies the sources for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

inetMRouteUpstreamNeighborType.name: inetMRouteUpstreamNeighborType
inetMRouteUpstreamNeighborType.description: A value indicating the address family of the address contained in inetMRouteUpstreamNeighbor. The value MUST be the same as the value of inetMRouteGroupType.

inetMRouteUpstreamNeighbor.name: inetMRouteUpstreamNeighbor
inetMRouteUpstreamNeighbor.description: The address of the upstream neighbor (e.g., RPF neighbor) from which IP datagrams from these sources to this multicast address are received. If the upstream neighbor is unknown, then inetMRouteUpstreamNeighbor will be 0.0.0.0 in the case of an IPv4 entry, and 0:0:0:0:0:0:0:0 in the case of an IPv6 entry. (e.g., in CBT).

inetMRouteInIfIndex.name: inetMRouteInIfIndex
inetMRouteInIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex for the interface on which IP datagrams sent by these sources to this multicast address are received. A value of 0 indicates that datagrams are not subject to an incoming interface check, but may be accepted on multiple interfaces (e.g., in CBT).

inetMRouteUpTime.name: inetMRouteUpTime
inetMRouteUpTime.description: The time since the multicast routing information represented by this entry was learned by the router.

inetMRouteExpiryTime.name: inetMRouteExpiryTime
inetMRouteExpiryTime.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before this entry will be aged out. The value 0 indicates that the entry is not subject to aging.

inetMRoutePkts.name: inetMRoutePkts
inetMRoutePkts.description: The number of packets which this router has received from these sources and addressed to this multicast group address.

inetMRouteDifferentInIfPackets.name: inetMRouteDifferentInIfPackets
inetMRouteDifferentInIfPackets.description: The number of packets which this router has received from these sources and addressed to this multicast group address, which were dropped because they were not received on the interface indicated by inetMRouteInIfIndex. Packets which are not subject to an incoming interface check (e.g., using CBT) are not counted.

inetMRouteOctets.name: inetMRouteOctets
inetMRouteOctets.description: The number of octets contained in IP datagrams which were received from these sources and addressed to this multicast group address, and which were forwarded by this router.

inetMRouteProtocol.name: inetMRouteProtocol
inetMRouteProtocol.description: The multicast routing protocol via which this multicast forwarding entry was learned.

inetMRouteRtProto.name: inetMRouteRtProto
inetMRouteRtProto.description: The routing mechanism via which the route used to find the upstream or parent interface for this multicast forwarding entry was learned. Inclusion of values for routing protocols is not intended to imply that those protocols need be supported.

inetMRouteRtAddressType.name: inetMRouteRtAddressType
inetMRouteRtAddressType.description: A value indicating the address family of the address contained in inetMRouteRtAddress. The value MUST be the same as the value of inetMRouteGroupType.

inetMRouteRtAddress.name: inetMRouteRtAddress
inetMRouteRtAddress.description: The address portion of the route used to find the upstream or parent interface for this multicast forwarding entry.

inetMRouteRtMaskLen.name: inetMRouteRtMaskLen
inetMRouteRtMaskLen.description: The length in bits of the mask associated with the route used to find the upstream or parent interface for this multicast forwarding entry.

inetMRouteRtType.name: inetMRouteRtType
inetMRouteRtType.description: The reason the given route was placed in the (logical) multicast Routing Information Base (RIB). A value of unicast means that the route would normally be placed only in the unicast RIB, but was placed in the multicast RIB (instead or in addition) due to local configuration, such as when running PIM over RIP. A value of multicast means that the route was explicitly added to the multicast RIB by the routing protocol, such as DVMRP or Multiprotocol BGP.

inetMRouteHCOctets.name: inetMRouteHCOctets
inetMRouteHCOctets.description: The number of octets contained in IP datagrams which were received from these sources and addressed to this multicast group address, and which were forwarded by this router. This object is a 64-bit version of inetMRouteOctets.

inetMRouteNextHopTable.name: inetMRouteNextHopTable
inetMRouteNextHopTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on the next-hops on outgoing interfaces for routing IP multicast datagrams. Each entry is one of a list of next-hops on outgoing interfaces for particular sources sending to a particular multicast group address.

inetMRouteNextHopEntry.name: inetMRouteNextHopEntry
inetMRouteNextHopEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the list of next-hops on outgoing interfaces to which IP multicast datagrams from particular sources to a IP multicast group address are routed. Discontinuities in counters in this entry can be detected by observing the value of inetMRouteUpTime.

inetMRouteNextHopGroupType.name: inetMRouteNextHopGroupType
inetMRouteNextHopGroupType.description: A value indicating the address family of the address contained in inetMRouteNextHopGroup. Legal values correspond to the subset of address families for which multicast forwarding is supported.

inetMRouteNextHopGroup.name: inetMRouteNextHopGroup
inetMRouteNextHopGroup.description: The IP multicast group for which this entry specifies a next-hop on an outgoing interface.

inetMRouteNextHopSourceType.name: inetMRouteNextHopSourceType
inetMRouteNextHopSourceType.description: A value indicating the address family of the address contained in inetMRouteNextHopSourceType. The value MUST be the same as the value of inetMRouteNextHopGroupType.

inetMRouteNextHopSource.name: inetMRouteNextHopSource
inetMRouteNextHopSource.description: The network address which when combined with the corresponding value of the mask specified in inetMRouteNextHopSourceMaskLen identifies the sources for which this entry specifies a next-hop on an outgoing interface.

inetMRouteNextHopSourceMaskLen.name: inetMRouteNextHopSourceMaskLen
inetMRouteNextHopSourceMaskLen.description: The length in bits of the mask which when combined with the corresponding value specified in inetMRouteNextHopSource identifies the sources for which this entry specifies a next-hop on an outgoing interface.

inetMRouteNextHopIfIndex.name: inetMRouteNextHopIfIndex
inetMRouteNextHopIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for the outgoing interface for this next-hop.

inetMRouteNextHopAddressType.name: inetMRouteNextHopAddressType
inetMRouteNextHopAddressType.description: A value indicating the address family of the address contained in inetMRouteNextHopAddressType. The value MUST be the same as the value of inetMRouteNextHopGroupType.

inetMRouteNextHopAddress.name: inetMRouteNextHopAddress
inetMRouteNextHopAddress.description: The address of the next-hop specific to this entry. For most interfaces, this is identical to inetMRouteNextHopGroup. NBMA interfaces, however, may have multiple next-hop addresses out a single outgoing interface.

inetMRouteNextHopPruned.name: inetMRouteNextHopPruned
inetMRouteNextHopPruned.description: An indication of whether the outgoing interface and next-hop represented by this entry is currently being used to forward IP datagrams. The value 'false' indicates it is currently being used; the value 'true' indicates it is not.

inetMRouteNextHopUpTime.name: inetMRouteNextHopUpTime
inetMRouteNextHopUpTime.description: The time since the multicast routing information represented by this entry was learned by the router.

inetMRouteNextHopExpiryTime.name: inetMRouteNextHopExpiryTime
inetMRouteNextHopExpiryTime.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before this entry will be aged out. If inetMRouteNextHopPruned is pruned(1), the remaining time until the prune expires and the state reverts to forwarding(2). Otherwise, the remaining time until this entry is removed from the table. The time remaining may be copied from inetMRouteExpiryTime if the protocol in use for this entry dos not specify next-hop timers. The value 0 indicates that the entry is not subject to aging.

inetMRouteNextHopClosestMemberHops.name: inetMRouteNextHopClosestMemberHops
inetMRouteNextHopClosestMemberHops.description: The minimum number of hops between this router and any member of this IP multicast group reached via this next-hop on this outgoing interface. Any IP multicast datagrams for the group which have a TTL (IPv4) or Hop Count (IPv6) less than this number of hops will not be forwarded to this next-hop.

inetMRouteNextHopProtocol.name: inetMRouteNextHopProtocol
inetMRouteNextHopProtocol.description: The routing mechanism via which this next-hop was learned.

inetMRouteNextHopPkts.name: inetMRouteNextHopPkts
inetMRouteNextHopPkts.description: The number of packets which have been forwarded using this route.

inetMRouteInterfaceTable.name: inetMRouteInterfaceTable
inetMRouteInterfaceTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing multicast routing information specific to interfaces.

inetMRouteInterfaceEntry.name: inetMRouteInterfaceEntry
inetMRouteInterfaceEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the multicast routing information for a particular interface.

inetMRouteInterfaceIfIndex.name: inetMRouteInterfaceIfIndex
inetMRouteInterfaceIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which this entry contains information.

inetMRouteInterfaceTtl.name: inetMRouteInterfaceTtl
inetMRouteInterfaceTtl.description: The datagram TTL threshold for the interface. Any IP multicast datagrams with a TTL (IPv4) or Hop Count (IPv6) less than this threshold will not be forwarded out the interface. The default value of 0 means all multicast packets are forwarded out the interface.

inetMRouteInterfaceProtocol.name: inetMRouteInterfaceProtocol
inetMRouteInterfaceProtocol.description: The routing protocol running on this interface.

inetMRouteInterfaceRateLimit.name: inetMRouteInterfaceRateLimit
inetMRouteInterfaceRateLimit.description: The rate-limit, in kilobits per second, of forwarded multicast traffic on the interface. A rate-limit of 0 indicates that no rate limiting is done.

inetMRouteInterfaceInMcastOctets.name: inetMRouteInterfaceInMcastOctets
inetMRouteInterfaceInMcastOctets.description: The number of octets of multicast packets that have arrived on the interface, including framing characters. This object is similar to ifInOctets in the Interfaces MIB, except that only multicast packets are counted.

inetMRouteInterfaceOutMcastOctets.name: inetMRouteInterfaceOutMcastOctets
inetMRouteInterfaceOutMcastOctets.description: The number of octets of multicast packets that have been sent on the interface.

inetMRouteInterfaceHCInMcastOctets.name: inetMRouteInterfaceHCInMcastOctets
inetMRouteInterfaceHCInMcastOctets.description: The number of octets of multicast packets that have arrived on the interface, including framing characters. This object is a 64-bit version of inetMRouteInterfaceInMcastOctets. It is similar to ifHCInOctets in the Interfaces MIB, except that only multicast packets are counted.

inetMRouteInterfaceHCOutMcastOctets.name: inetMRouteInterfaceHCOutMcastOctets
inetMRouteInterfaceHCOutMcastOctets.description: The number of octets of multicast packets that have been sent on the interface. This object is a 64-bit version of inetMRouteInterfaceOutMcastOctets.

inetMRouteBoundaryTable.name: inetMRouteBoundaryTable
inetMRouteBoundaryTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the router's scoped multicast address boundaries.

inetMRouteBoundaryEntry.name: inetMRouteBoundaryEntry
inetMRouteBoundaryEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the inetMRouteBoundaryTable representing a scoped boundary.

inetMRouteBoundaryIfIndex.name: inetMRouteBoundaryIfIndex
inetMRouteBoundaryIfIndex.description: The IfIndex value for the interface to which this boundary applies. Packets with a destination address in the associated address/mask range will not be forwarded out this interface.

inetMRouteBoundaryAddressType.name: inetMRouteBoundaryAddressType
inetMRouteBoundaryAddressType.description: A value indicating the address family of the address contained in inetMRouteBoundaryAddress. Legal values correspond to the subset of address families for which multicast forwarding is supported.

inetMRouteBoundaryAddress.name: inetMRouteBoundaryAddress
inetMRouteBoundaryAddress.description: The group address which when combined with the corresponding value of inetMRouteBoundaryAddressMaskLen identifies the group range for which the scoped boundary exists. Scoped IPv4 addresses must come from the range 239.x.x.x as specified in RFC 2365. Scoped IPv6 addresses must come from range ff.nn.nn.nn.nn.nn.nn.nn, where nn encodes the scope type and group identifier as specified in RFC 2373.

inetMRouteBoundaryAddressMaskLen.name: inetMRouteBoundaryAddressMaskLen
inetMRouteBoundaryAddressMaskLen.description: The length in bits of the mask which when combined with the corresponding value of inetMRouteBoundaryAddress identifies the group range for which the scoped boundary exists.

inetMRouteBoundaryStatus.name: inetMRouteBoundaryStatus
inetMRouteBoundaryStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

inetMRouteScopeNameTable.name: inetMRouteScopeNameTable
inetMRouteScopeNameTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the multicast scope names.

inetMRouteScopeNameEntry.name: inetMRouteScopeNameEntry
inetMRouteScopeNameEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the inetMRouteScopeNameTable representing a multicast scope name.

inetMRouteScopeNameAddressType.name: inetMRouteScopeNameAddressType
inetMRouteScopeNameAddressType.description: A value indicating the address family of the address contained in inetMRouteScopeNameAddressType. Legal values correspond to the subset of address families for which multicast forwarding is supported.

inetMRouteScopeNameAddress.name: inetMRouteScopeNameAddress
inetMRouteScopeNameAddress.description: The group address which when combined with the corresponding value of inetMRouteScopeNameAddressMaskLen identifies the group range associated with the multicast scope. Scoped IPv4 addresses must come from the range 239.x.x.x. Scoped IPv6 addresses must come from range ff.nn.nn.nn.nn.nn.nn.nn, where nn encodes the scope type and group identifier as specified in RFC 2373.

inetMRouteScopeNameAddressMaskLen.name: inetMRouteScopeNameAddressMaskLen
inetMRouteScopeNameAddressMaskLen.description: The length in bits of the mask which when combined with the corresponding value of inetMRouteScopeNameAddress identifies the group range associated with the multicast scope.

inetMRouteScopeNameLanguage.name: inetMRouteScopeNameLanguage
inetMRouteScopeNameLanguage.description: The RFC 1766-style language tag associated with the scope name.

inetMRouteScopeNameString.name: inetMRouteScopeNameString
inetMRouteScopeNameString.description: The textual name associated with the multicast scope. The value of this object should be suitable for displaying to end-users, such as when allocating a multicast address in this scope. When no name is specified, the default value of this object for IPv4 should be the string 239.x.x.x/y with x and y replaced appropriately to describe the address and mask length associated with the scope. Scoped IPv6 addresses must come from range ff.nn.nn.nn.nn.nn.nn.nn, where nn encodes the scope type and group identifier.

inetMRouteScopeNameDefault.name: inetMRouteScopeNameDefault
inetMRouteScopeNameDefault.description: If true, indicates a preference that the name in the following language should be used by applications if no name is available in a desired language.

inetMRouteScopeNameStatus.name: inetMRouteScopeNameStatus
inetMRouteScopeNameStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

inetMRouteMIBCompliance.name: inetMRouteMIBCompliance
inetMRouteMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the IP Multicast MIB.

inetMRouteMIBBasicGroup.name: inetMRouteMIBBasicGroup
inetMRouteMIBBasicGroup.description: A collection of objects to support basic management of IP Multicast routing.

inetMRouteMIBHopCountGroup.name: inetMRouteMIBHopCountGroup
inetMRouteMIBHopCountGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of the use of hop counts in IP Multicast routing.

inetMRouteMIBBoundaryGroup.name: inetMRouteMIBBoundaryGroup
inetMRouteMIBBoundaryGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of scoped multicast address boundaries.

inetMRouteMIBPktsOutGroup.name: inetMRouteMIBPktsOutGroup
inetMRouteMIBPktsOutGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of packet counters for each outgoing interface entry of a route.

inetMRouteMIBHCInterfaceGroup.name: inetMRouteMIBHCInterfaceGroup
inetMRouteMIBHCInterfaceGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information specific to high speed (greater than 20,000,000 bits/second) network interfaces.

inetMRouteMIBRouteGroup.name: inetMRouteMIBRouteGroup
inetMRouteMIBRouteGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information on the relationship between multicast routing information, and the IP Forwarding Table.

inetMRouteMIBPktsGroup.name: inetMRouteMIBPktsGroup
inetMRouteMIBPktsGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of packet counters for each forwarding entry.
